Subject: [PATCH] perf: hardware-optimised tuning, Groq fast path, speculative
 decoding
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Tuned for i5-10400H / 16 GB DDR4-2933 / no discrete GPU.

docker-compose.yml
- LLAMA_ARG_THREADS_BATCH: 4 → 8 (use HT for prompt eval; compute-bound)
- LLAMA_ARG_CTX_SIZE default: 4096 → 2048 (halves KV cache)
- localbot memory limit: 6G → 8G (headroom for larger model + draft)
- localbot CPU limit: 3.0 → 4.0 (use all physical cores)
- Expanded inline comments explaining each tuning decision and why
  LLAMA_ARG_N_GPU_LAYERS must stay 0 on Intel UHD (shared DDR4 bus)

src/localbot/adapters/groq_client.py (new)
- Thin async Groq API client (OpenAI-compatible)
- Supports streaming via on_token callback, matching LlamaCppClient interface
- Falls back cleanly on any HTTP error

src/localbot/intent.py
- Add is_groq_eligible(): blocks filesystem, scheduler, diagnostic queries
  from ever leaving the device; allows general chat and search synthesis

src/localbot/config.py
- Add groq_api_key, groq_model fields
- Add cloudflare_account_id, cloudflare_api_token fields
- Add slot_draft_model, slot_draft_max for speculative decoding config
- Update search defaults: result_count 5→8, fetch_count 3→5, fetch_chars 1500→2000

src/localbot/adapters/llamacpp_server.py
- Append --model-draft / --draft-max / --draft-min args when slot_draft_model set

src/localbot/agent.py
- Instantiate GroqClient in __init__ when GROQ_API_KEY is configured
- Extract _run_local() helper to deduplicate local model acquisition logic
- Add Groq fast path in handle(): routes eligible, tool-free queries to Groq;
  falls back to local on any Groq error; never routes sensitive queries off-device

src/localbot/app.py
- Close GroqClient on bot shutdown

.env.example
- Add GROQ_API_KEY, CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID, CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN
- Add SLOT_DRAFT_MODEL with speculative decoding guidance
- Update model slot recommendations (3B general, 4B MoE coding, 7B reasoning)
- Update LLAMA_SERVER_EXTRA_ARGS default with flash-attn, q8_0 KV cache, ubatch-size
- Update LLAMA_CTX_SIZE default: 4096 → 2048
- Update search count/fetch defaults

README.md
- New Performance Tuning section with hardware-specific rationale table
- New Speculative Decoding section with RAM budget table
- New Groq Fast Path section with privacy policy and routing explanation
- Updated model recommendations table with tok/s estimates
- Updated docker-compose tuning comments
- Updated project layout to include groq_client.py
